Version 2.9: 
 - [!] 24 Jul 2006, Alien - Bug (0023391): AntiFraud data was not stored properly in encrypted orders. Fixed.

Version 2.8: 
 - [+] 29 May 2007, Osipov - Improvement (0019852): The user interface was improved to prohibit the use of offline CC payment method when AdvancedSecurity is not configured.

Version 2.7: 
 - [+] 26 Dec 2006, Osipov - Improvement (0014523): The user interface was improved to avoid module misusing when AdvancedSecurity is not configured.
 - [+] 26 Dec 2006, Osipov - Improvement (0009310): When AdvancedSecurity is not configured, manual CC processing cannot be used.

Version 2.6: 
 - [+] 12 Jul 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0007087): New security option ("Clear master password after login and logoff") was added.
 - [!] 16 Jun 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0004131): A few typos were fixed.
 - [+] 22 Nov 2005, Sheriff - Improvement (0004945): Code optimization was made to avoid warnings being displayed that "open_basedir" restriction is in effect.

Version 2.5: 
 - [!] 19 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0003855): Additional order details data was being lost after decryption which in some cases resulted in incorrect operation of other modules (e.g. AntiFraud). Fixed.

Version 2.4: 
 - [!] 05 Aug 2005, Sheriff - Bug (0003726): If a customer used manual credit card processing after unsuccessfully trying to use online credit card processing, the CC details were not stored. Fixed.
 - [!] 07 Mar 2005, Asd - Bug: The compiled code/templates cache was not cleaned up during the module uninstallation. Fixed.

Version 2.3:
 - [!] 2004-12-30, Sheriff - Bug: The error messages that displayed on "stderr" were not always suppressed. Fixed.
